FBIS4-16025 "drsov071_a_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-071 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Yeltsin Fears Air Strikes To Exacerbate Bosnian Conflict Yeltsin Fears Air Strikes To Exacerbate Bosnian Conflict LD1204220394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 2044 GMT 12 Apr 94 LD1204220394 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [From the "Diplomatic Panorama" feature: Reports by Diplomatic Correspondents Igor Porshnev, Vitaliy Trubetskoy, and others] [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin expressed the hope that the NATO air strikes against Serbian positions near Gorazde would not contribute to confrontations or increase the scale of the bloodshed. He told an INTERFAX correspondent in Madrid Tuesday that Russia will keep in touch with Butrus Butrus-Ghali and Bill Clinton to avoid a repetition of the incident.
